# METERP code rules

## Multi-tenancy (critical)
- Tenant-scoped entities use `BaseEntity`; respect `AppDbContext` global filters.
- Set `TenantId` from `ITenantProvider` in services — never hardcode tenant IDs.
- Soft-delete via `IsDeleted`; do not physically delete tenant business data unless explicitly required.

## New features checklist
1. Domain entity/enum
2. `Application/Services/I*Service.cs`
3. `Infrastructure/Services/*Service.cs`
4. `Program.cs` DI + authorization policy
5. `Common/Permissions.cs` constants
6. Blazor page in `Web/Components/Pages/`
7. Nav entry in `NavMenu.razor` if user-facing
8. EF migration for schema changes (`dotnet ef migrations add` from Infrastructure project)

## Patterns to match
- `LineTotal` on document lines is computed in the entity, not assigned in UI.
- Usage counters on `Tenant` increment in service create methods.
- Check `tenant.HasFeature("ai")` before AI operations.
- Seeding: safe by default; only reset with `METERP_SEED_RESET=true`.
- UI: `professional.css`, `ToastService`, `@rendermode InteractiveServer`, reuse `QuoteList`/`JobList` gateway patterns.

## Testing
- Run `dotnet test` after non-trivial changes.
- Add unit tests for calculation logic in `tests/METERP.Application.Tests/`.

## Avoid
- Business logic in Razor `@code` blocks — delegate to services.
- Bypassing tenant filters or cross-layer references.
- SQL Server — use PostgreSQL/Npgsql only.
- Unrelated refactors in the same PR as a feature fix.